3.10	Mail_slot	Letter box	A letter box, letterbox, letter plate, letter hole, mail slot, or mailbox is a receptacle for receiving incoming mail at a private residence or business. For the opposite purpose of collating outgoing mail, a post box is generally used instead.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Black_door.jpg/200px-Black_door.jpg
